div1.p: IN THE UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT FOR THE WESTERN SISTRICT OF WASHINGTON, NOTHTERN DIVISION
In the Matter of the Application of MRS. GLADYS FREDRIKS FUSON, for the Writ of Habeas Corpu} No.3451 ORDER

Upon reading and filing the Affidavit and Petition of GLadys Fredriks Fuson, the application for habeas corpus herein, for permission to prosecute daid proceding in fprman pauperis, and having been duly advised in the premises,

ORDERED that the petition be granted, and that all of the procedings hertofore had may be entered by the Clerk if this Court as in forma pauperis, and that any deposits made by the petitioner in this action be return to her by the CLerk
DONE IN OPEN COURT this 2nd day of November AD 1916
U.S. SDistrict Court Western District of Washington Northern Division
In Re Gladys Fuson's Application for Wrif of Habeas Corpus
FILED IN THE U.S District Court, Western Dist. of Wshington, NORTHERN DIVISION Nov 2-1916 FRANK L. CROSBY, Clerk By HC Deputy
